4 HR____ COMMENDING WENONAH HIGH SCHOOL BOYS BASKETBALL TEAM
5 FOR WINNING THE 2026 ALABAMA HIGH SCHOOL ATHLETIC
6 ASSOCIATION 5A STATE CHAMPIONSHIP.
7
8 WHEREAS, highest commendations are herein proudly
9 presented to the Wenonah High School Boys Basketball Team
10 from Birmingham, Alabama, on winning the 2026 Alabama High
11 School Athletic Association (AHSAA) 5A State Championship on
12 March 7, 2026, at Legacy Arena in Birmingham; and
13 WHEREAS, through teamwork, diligence, and a
14 commitment to excellence, the Wenonah High School Dragons
15 took the 101-40 victory over Sylacauga, making history as
16 the first AHSAA boys team to score 100 points in a title
17 game; the 61-point win set a new AHSAA all-time record for
18 the largest margin of victory in a title game; and
19 WHEREAS, Brendon Davis was named the Tournament Most
20 Valuable Player after an extraordinary performance,
21 supported by All-Tournament Team selections Jaurice Smith,
22 Santez Pendleton, and Demazzia Taylor; and
23 WHEREAS, this victory marks the seventh state title
24 in the storied history of Wenonah High School basketball;
25 Wenonah's victory avenged a 69-68 loss to Sylacauga in last
26 year's Class 5A semifinals; the win reflects a tradition of
27 excellence, discipline, and community pride; and
28 WHEREAS, Brendon Davis led Wenonah with 42 points and
Page 1

WHEREAS, Brendon Davis led Wenonah with 42 points and
